\title{"speech"}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{"Use when the user asks for text-to-speech narration or voiceover, accessibility reads, audio prompts, or batch speech generation via the OpenAI Audio API; run the bundled CLI (`scripts/text_to_speech.py`) with built-in voices and require `OPENAI_API_KEY` for live calls. Custom voice creation is out of scope."}

\subtree{
\title{Speech Generation Skill}
\p{Generate spoken audio for the current project (narration, product demo voiceover, IVR prompts, accessibility reads). Defaults to \code{\startverb gpt-4o-mini-tts-2025-12-15\stopverb} and built-in voices, and prefers the bundled CLI for deterministic, reproducible runs.}

\subtree{
\title{When to use}
\ul{
\li{Generate a single spoken clip from text}
\li{Generate a batch of prompts (many lines, many files)}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Decision tree (single vs batch)}
\ul{
\li{If the user provides multiple lines/prompts or wants many outputs -> \strong{batch}}
\li{Else -> \strong{single}}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Workflow}
\ol{
\li{Decide intent: single vs batch (see decision tree above).}
\li{Collect inputs up front: exact text (verbatim), desired voice, delivery style, format, and any constraints.}
\li{If batch: write a temporary JSONL under tmp/ (one job per line), run once, then delete the JSONL.}
\li{Augment instructions into a short labeled spec without rewriting the input text.}
\li{Run the bundled CLI (\code{\startverb scripts/text_to_speech.py\stopverb}) with sensible defaults (see references/cli.md).}
\li{For important clips, validate: intelligibility, pacing, pronunciation, and adherence to constraints.}
\li{Iterate with a single targeted change (voice, speed, or instructions), then re-check.}
\li{Save/return final outputs and note the final text + instructions + flags used.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Temp and output conventions}
\ul{
\li{Use \code{\startverb tmp/speech/\stopverb} for intermediate files (for example JSONL batches); delete when done.}
\li{Write final artifacts under \code{\startverb output/speech/\stopverb} when working in this repo.}
\li{Use \code{\startverb --out\stopverb} or \code{\startverb --out-dir\stopverb} to control output paths; keep filenames stable and descriptive.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Dependencies (install if missing)}
\p{Prefer \code{\startverb uv\stopverb} for dependency management.}

\p{Python packages:}

\pre{\startverb
uv pip install openai
\stopverb}

\p{If \code{\startverb uv\stopverb} is unavailable:}

\pre{\startverb
python3 -m pip install openai
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Environment}
\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb OPENAI_API_KEY\stopverb} must be set for live API calls.}
}

\p{If the key is missing, give the user these steps:}

\ol{
\li{Create an API key in the OpenAI platform UI: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys}
\li{Set \code{\startverb OPENAI_API_KEY\stopverb} as an environment variable in their system.}
\li{Offer to guide them through setting the environment variable for their OS/shell if needed.}
}

\ul{
\li{Never ask the user to paste the full key in chat. Ask them to set it locally and confirm when ready.}
}

\p{If installation isn't possible in this environment, tell the user which dependency is missing and how to install it locally.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Defaults & rules}
\ul{
\li{Use \code{\startverb gpt-4o-mini-tts-2025-12-15\stopverb} unless the user requests another model.}
\li{Default voice: \code{\startverb cedar\stopverb}. If the user wants a brighter tone, prefer \code{\startverb marin\stopverb}.}
\li{Built-in voices only. Custom voices are out of scope for this skill.}
\li{\code{\startverb instructions\stopverb} are supported for GPT-4o mini TTS models, but not for \code{\startverb tts-1\stopverb} or \code{\startverb tts-1-hd\stopverb}.}
\li{Input length must be <= 4096 characters per request. Split longer text into chunks.}
\li{Enforce 50 requests/minute. The CLI caps \code{\startverb --rpm\stopverb} at 50.}
\li{Require \code{\startverb OPENAI_API_KEY\stopverb} before any live API call.}
\li{Provide a clear disclosure to end users that the voice is AI-generated.}
\li{Use the OpenAI Python SDK (\code{\startverb openai\stopverb} package) for all API calls; do not use raw HTTP.}
\li{Prefer the bundled CLI (\code{\startverb scripts/text_to_speech.py\stopverb}) over writing new one-off scripts.}
\li{Never modify \code{\startverb scripts/text_to_speech.py\stopverb}. If something is missing, ask the user before doing anything else.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Instruction augmentation}
\p{Reformat user direction into a short, labeled spec. Only make implicit details explicit; do not invent new requirements.}

\p{Quick clarification (augmentation vs invention):}

\ul{
\li{If the user says "narration for a demo", you may add implied delivery constraints (clear, steady pacing, friendly tone).}
\li{Do not introduce a new persona, accent, or emotional style the user did not request.}
}

\p{Template (include only relevant lines):}

\pre{\startverb
Voice Affect: <overall character and texture of the voice>
Tone: <attitude, formality, warmth>
Pacing: <slow, steady, brisk>
Emotion: <key emotions to convey>
Pronunciation: <words to enunciate or emphasize>
Pauses: <where to add intentional pauses>
Emphasis: <key words or phrases to stress>
Delivery: <cadence or rhythm notes>
\stopverb}

\p{Augmentation rules:}

\ul{
\li{Keep it short; add only details the user already implied or provided elsewhere.}
\li{Do not rewrite the input text.}
\li{If any critical detail is missing and blocks success, ask a question; otherwise proceed.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Examples}
\subtree{
\title{Single example (narration)}
\pre{\startverb
Input text: "Welcome to the demo. Today we'll show how it works."
Instructions:
Voice Affect: Warm and composed.
Tone: Friendly and confident.
Pacing: Steady and moderate.
Emphasis: Stress "demo" and "show".
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Batch example (IVR prompts)}
\pre{\startverb
{"input":"Thank you for calling. Please hold.","voice":"cedar","response_format":"mp3","out":"hold.mp3"}
{"input":"For sales, press 1. For support, press 2.","voice":"marin","instructions":"Tone: Clear and neutral. Pacing: Slow.","response_format":"wav"}
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Instructioning best practices (short list)}
\ul{
\li{Structure directions as: affect -> tone -> pacing -> emotion -> pronunciation/pauses -> emphasis.}
\li{Keep 4 to 8 short lines; avoid conflicting guidance.}
\li{For names/acronyms, add pronunciation hints (e.g., "enunciate A-I") or supply a phonetic spelling in the text.}
\li{For edits/iterations, repeat invariants (e.g., "keep pacing steady") to reduce drift.}
\li{Iterate with single-change follow-ups.}
}

\p{More principles: \code{\startverb references/prompting.md\stopverb}. Copy/paste specs: \code{\startverb references/sample-prompts.md\stopverb}.}
}

